# Justfile / Scripts Alignment

The `justfile` is a convenience wrapper around scripts in `scripts/`. Keep them in sync:

- Every script in `scripts/` must have a corresponding recipe in the `justfile`
- Every recipe in the `justfile` (except `default`) must delegate to a script in `scripts/`
- When a script is added, renamed, or removed, update the `justfile` to match
- Recipe comments in the `justfile` should match the one-line description from the script's header

## Current mapping

| Script | Recipe |
|--------|--------|
| `scripts/build.sh` | `build` |
| `scripts/install.sh` | `install` |
| `scripts/test.sh` | `test` |
| `scripts/test-mcp.sh` | `test-mcp` |
| `scripts/reset.sh` | `reset` |
| `scripts/kill.sh` | `kill` |
| `scripts/uninstall.sh` | `uninstall` |
